HTML - Hyper text markup language

- to create a webpage
- not a programming language
- Its a markup language
- Every webpage starts with HTML

1. Heading - h1 - h6

2. paragraph - p

3. hr

4. br

5. text formating
   u, i,, b or strong, mark, sub and sup

6. anchor tag - a

7. image tag - img

8. list
   order list and unorder list

9. tables - th, tr, td

10. forms
    label and input

CSS - Cascading Style Sheet

1. Types of css
   i - inline
   ii - internal
   iii- external

inline > internal > external

2. Css syntax
   selector {
   property: value;
   }

3. types of selectors
   i- element selector - (p), (h1)...
   ii - class selector - (.) multiple , number of times
   iii - id selector - (#) unique , only one time(name)
   iv - universal selector - (\*)
   v - group selector - (h1,h2)

4. colors and background
   background-color : gold;
   color : silver;
   background-image : url();
   background-repeat: no-repeat;
   background-size: cover;
   background-position: center;

5. text styling
   font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;
   font-size: 40px;
   text-align: center;
   text-transform: uppercase;
   text-decoration: line-through;
   font-weight: bold;
   line-height: 2;
   letter-spacing: 2px;

6. Box modeling
   i - content
   ii - padding
   iii - border
   iv - margin

7. flex
   direction - row, row-reverse, column, column-reverse

justify content (x) - start, center, end, space-around, space-between, space-evenly

align items (y) - start, center, end

flex wrap - no-wrap, wrap, wrap-reverse

align-content - start, center, end, space-around, space-between, space-evenly

gap - to assgin value

flex(on items) - its grow to actual ratio

order - change the visual order of the flex

8. position
   i - Static - default -
   ii - relative - to set the direction value
   iii - absolute - depents upon the non-Static parents
   iv - fiexed - to fix the web pages
   v - sticky - same to the fiexed

9. Grid - 2 dimensional layout system 

10. Transition and Animation

11. Media Queries(Resposive design)

MOBILE - 320px - 600px
TAB - 601px - 800px
LAP/DESKTOP - 801px <=